author: Russell Brand
description:
Robots that can recharge themselves. AI programs that lie. Billionaires warning of an “imminent threat to humanity.” What looks like sci-fi is fast becoming reality—and the narratives around it are being shaped to keep us fearful, compliant, or distracted. In this unpacking, I explore the rise of humanoid robotics in China and the U.S., the propaganda that comes with it, and the deeper question of what separates intelligence from consciousness. Are we heading toward an AI apocalypse—or just another excuse for elites to consolidate power?
